The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Nov. 28: Telecom tribunal TDSAT today dismissed VSNL?s petition and upheld the Trai order on reduction of bandwidth prices. It also asked the regulator to implement the order immediately. ?We dismiss this appeal and direct that the notification in question be brought into effect immediately by Trai so that the benefit of the notification to the consumer is not delayed. The appeal is dismissed with cost computed at Rs 50,000,? TDSAT said.

 Mumbai, Nov. 28: Reserve Bank chief economist Narendra Jadhav today said the combined fiscal deficits of Union territories and state governments is expected to come down to 5.5 per cent, while that of the Centre to 3 per cent in 2008-09.

 New Delhi, Nov. 28: The steel ministry is reviewing the recommendations of the expert committee on iron ore regarding the allocation of ore to steel firms, said steel minister Ram Vilas Paswan.

 New Delhi, Nov. 28: Nicholas Piramal India Ltd (NPIL) today said the company was looking for acquisitions in the UK and North America.

 London, Nov. 28: HSBC Holdings CEO Stephen Green will become chairman, replacing John Bond, the architect of more than $46 billion of acquisitions.




